==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Capillament
<hw>Ca*pil"la*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>capillamentum</ets>, fr. <ets>capillus</ets> hair: cf. F.
<ets>capillament</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
filament.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Any villous or hairy covering; a
fine fiber or filament, as of the nerves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Capillariness</ent>⟦br⟧
